The policy is up to me and I've said yes, so it done. Ok?

328
00:20:15,047 --> 00:20:16,924
汉弗莱怎么了?
What's the matter with Humphrey?

329
00:20:17,647 --> 00:20:20,161
我没犯什么错吧?
I haven't done anything wrong, have I?

330
00:20:20,847 --> 00:20:24,283
不会真有安全问题吧?
There aren't any security Implications, are there?

331
00:20:24,447 --> 00:20:25,846
到底搞什么?
What's the problem?

332
00:20:27,767 --> 00:20:30,964
我在自言自语吗?      不 大臣 我听着呢
Am I talking to myself? No, I'm listening.

333
00:20:31,127 --> 00:20:32,480
怎么不回答?
Why don't you answer?

334
00:20:32,647 --> 00:20:35,605
抱歉 我以为您这是设问句
I thought your questions were purely rhetorical.

335
00:20:35,767 --> 00:20:38,327
我也不明白他紧张什么
I see no reason for him to be so anxious.

336
00:20:38,487 --> 00:20:39,761
除非...
Unless...

337
00:20:41,767 --> 00:20:45,965
你跟我想的一样吗?      我想不会 大臣
Are you thinking what I'm thinking? I don't think so, Minister.

338
00:20:47,607 --> 00:20:49,598
我什么都没在想
I'm not thinking anything, really.

339
00:20:50,487 --> 00:20:52,398
我想我闻到耗子味了
I begin to smell a rat.

340
00:20:52,567 --> 00:20:55,161
要我找卫生官员来吗?
Shall I get an environmental health officer?

341
00:20:59,047 --> 00:21:02,244
汉弗莱在行政部干了多久?
How long has Sir Humphrey been here at Administrative Affairs?

342
00:21:02,407 --> 00:21:05,001
从建部开始      那是什么时候?
Since it was founded. When was that?

343
00:21:05,167 --> 00:21:09,240
1964年 就跟经济部一起...
1964. The same time they started the Department for Economic...

344
00:21:11,527 --> 00:21:14,087
现在我跟您想的一样了
Now I think I'm thinking what you're thinking.

345
00:21:14,247 --> 00:21:15,600
你在想什么?
And what are you thinking?

346
00:21:15,767 --> 00:21:18,600
您在想 他1964年前在哪里
You're thinking, where was he before 1964?

347
00:21:18,767 --> 00:21:20,564
花名册里有记载
It'll be in "Who's Who".

348
00:21:20,727 --> 00:21:24,925
一定在别的部门 被网罗到行政部的
He must've been in another department and trawled for the DAA.

349
00:21:25,087 --> 00:21:28,682
什么?      网罗 拿网子捞鱼
What? Trawled. Fished, caught in the net.

350
00:21:29,687 --> 00:21:32,679
啊 找到了 我的天啊      怎么?
Ah, here we are. Oh, my God! What?

351
00:21:34,007 --> 00:21:39,240
1950-56年 他是苏格兰事务部副主管
He was Assistant Principal at the Scottish Office.

352
00:21:40,927 --> 00:21:43,646
从陆军部借调的
On secondment from the War Office.

353
00:21:46,487 --> 00:21:49,479
地区合同承办官
Regional Contracts Officer.

354
00:21:49,647 --> 00:21:51,763
30年前啊
30 years ago.

355
00:21:53,967 --> 00:21:56,162
原来这名官员
So the official...

356
00:21:56,327 --> 00:21:59,558
拱手送出4千万
who chucked away 40 million...

357
00:21:59,727 --> 00:22:02,525
纳税人的钱的...
of taxpayers' money was...

358
00:22:04,367 --> 00:22:06,562
真吓人
How frightful!

359
00:22:08,367 --> 00:22:11,564
太可怕了 大臣      恐怖
it抯 awful, Minister. Dreadful.

360
00:22:12,927 --> 00:22:16,966
所有档案几星期内就要解密了
And all the papers due for release in a few weeks' time.

361
00:22:18,927 --> 00:22:21,760
叫汉弗莱马上回来
Get Humphrey to come back here at once.

362
00:22:21,927 --> 00:22:23,121
是 大臣
Yes, Minister.

363
00:22:25,407 --> 00:22:28,319
格拉汉 我是伯纳 大臣问汉弗莱爵士是否
The Minister wonders if Sir Humphrey could spare time

364
00:22:28,487 --> 00:22:31,001
有空来开个会 几天之内
for a meeting sometime in the next few days.

365
00:22:31,167 --> 00:22:34,364
马上      其实 就在今天之内
At once. In fact, sometime today is really...

366
00:22:34,527 --> 00:22:38,520
马上      准确说 未来60秒之内
At once! Sometime during the next 60 seconds.

367
00:22:43,327 --> 00:22:46,922
他这就过来      怎么 他没晕啊?
He's coming round now. Why? Did he faint?

368
00:22:50,247 --> 00:22:53,523
不 他就...      这事很严重 伯纳
No, he's just, you know... This is serious, Bernard.

369
00:22:53,687 --> 00:22:55,166
对 我知道
Yes, I know.

370
00:22:58,207 --> 00:23:01,597
一点都不好笑      当然不好笑
This is no laughing matter. No, certainly not.

371
00:23:10,287 --> 00:23:11,959
问题在于
The question is...

372
00:23:13,607 --> 00:23:15,996
我要怎么处理呢?
how am I gong to deal with it?

373
00:23:16,167 --> 00:23:19,398
依我看...      这回是设问句 伯纳
In my opinion... The question was rhetorical.

374
00:23:22,967 --> 00:23:27,518
您找我 大臣?      汉弗莱 进来进来
You wanted a word, Minister? Humphrey, come in, come in.

375
00:23:30,447 --> 00:23:32,244
抱歉 伯纳
Sorry, Bernard.

376
00:23:40,047 --> 00:23:43,437
我在想苏格兰海岛丑闻的事
I've been thinking about this Scottish Island scandal.

377
00:23:44,927 --> 00:23:47,680
真让人担心      我不觉得...
Very worrying. Well, I don't know...

378
00:23:47,847 --> 00:23:49,565
你大概没意识到
You probably don't realise this,

379
00:23:49,727 --> 00:23:53,163
可这责任人很可能还在做公务员
but that official could still be in the Civil Servlce.

380
00:23:54,247 --> 00:23:56,238
应该不会      怎么不会?
Very unlikely. But why?

381
00:23:56,407 --> 00:24:01,003
他当年大概20多岁 现在正好50多岁
He could've been in his mld-20s then, he'd be in his mld-50s now.

382
00:24:01,167 --> 00:24:03,965
没准还当常任秘书了呢
Might even be a Permanent Secretary!

383
00:24:05,087 --> 00:24:08,124
我真不觉得...      也是 你说的对
I hardly think... No, of course, you're right.

384
00:24:08,287 --> 00:24:12,678
这么不靠谱的人怎能当常任秘书呢
Nobody who made a blunder become a Permanent Secretary.

385
00:24:12,847 --> 00:24:18,160
总之我要调查到底      大臣 这种事查不到
I want an investigation. Can't find out that sort of thing.

386
00:24:18,327 --> 00:24:19,555
当然查得到
Surely we can.

387
00:24:19,727 --> 00:24:23,606
你说的 凡事都有记录 有档案
You said yourself that minutes are always made, records kept

388
00:24:23,767 --> 00:24:25,564
在公务员系统里面
in the Civil Servlce.

389
00:24:25,727 --> 00:24:28,605
现行合同的法律文件
And legal documents concerning a current contract

390
00:24:28,767 --> 00:24:31,122
总不会丢掉吧
wouldn't have been thrown away.

391
00:24:32,127 --> 00:24:37,326
大臣 用不用搞得这么严重呢?
Minister... aren抰 we making a little too much of this?

392
00:24:37,487 --> 00:24:41,560
可能会毁掉一份光明前程 就为...
Possibly blighting a brilliant career because of a...

393
00:24:41,727 --> 00:24:43,604
30年前一点小疏忽?
tiny slip 30 years ago?

394
00:24:43,767 --> 00:24:46,725
反正 也没浪费很多钱嘛
After all, it抯 not such a lot of money wasted.

395
00:24:46,887 --> 00:24:48,286
4千万磅?
40 million?

396
00:24:50,047 --> 00:24:52,845
这个 您比比蓝光导弹
Well, not compared with Blue Streak,

397
00:24:53,007 --> 00:24:56,477
TSR2轰炸机 三叉戟客机 协和飞机
TSR.2, Trident, Concorde,

398
00:24:56,647 --> 00:24:59,081
政务理事会大楼
high-rise council flats,

399
00:24:59,247 --> 00:25:01,841
英国铁路
British Rail,

400
00:25:02,007 --> 00:25:04,077
英国利兰汽车 英国钢铁
British Leyland, British Steel,

401
00:25:04,807 --> 00:25:06,798
上克莱德造船厂
Upper Clyde Shipbuilders,

402
00:25:07,847 --> 00:25:11,681
原子能电站 公立综合中学
the atomic PowerStation programme, comprehensive schools,

403
00:25:11,847 --> 00:25:14,236
艾塞克斯大学
the University of Essex.

404
00:25:16,007 --> 00:25:20,205
对 我明白 不过它还是百倍地超出
I take your point, but it抯 still more, a hundred times more,

405
00:25:20,367 --> 00:25:23,757
这名官员一辈子能挣的工资
than this official could ever have earned in his entire career.

406
00:25:23,927 --> 00:25:28,842
因此我就交给你调查 找出谁干的
So I want you to look into it and find out who it was.

407
00:25:30,087 --> 00:25:31,406
好吗?
Ok?

408
00:25:40,407 --> 00:25:43,956
怎么了 汉弗莱?      大臣 有件事您得知道
Yes, Humphrey? There is something you ought to know.

409
00:25:45,087 --> 00:25:46,679
什么 汉弗莱?
Yes, Humphrey?

410
00:25:48,247 --> 00:25:51,125
被归置责任的这名官员的身份
The identity of the official whose alleged responsibility

411
00:25:51,287 --> 00:25:52,959
其作出这件假定的疏忽
for this hypothetical oversight,

412
00:25:53,127 --> 00:25:55,595
成为我们近来讨论的对象
as being the subject of recent discussion,

413
00:25:55,767 --> 00:25:59,601
并未笼罩在密不透风的层层迷雾之中
Is not shrouded in quite such impenetrable obscurity

414
00:25:59,767 --> 00:26:02,804
大异您基于早先信息作出的推断
as previous disclosures led you to assume.

415
00:26:02,967 --> 00:26:05,561
一言以蔽之 追根究底
But not to put too fine a point on it...

416
00:26:06,567 --> 00:26:10,162
我们讨论的这个人 也许您会吃惊
the individual in question is, It may surprise you to learn,

417
00:26:10,327 --> 00:26:13,524
在您目前的谈话对象提到他时
one whom your present interlocutor...

418
00:26:15,447 --> 00:26:17,642
通常会使用
Is in the habit of defining...

419
00:26:18,927 --> 00:26:21,725
第一人称代词来指代
by means of the perpendicular pronoun.

420
00:26:27,287 --> 00:26:29,278
你说什么?
I beg your pardon?

421
00:26:32,087 --> 00:26:34,681
这人是...我
It was... I.

422
00:26:36,127 --> 00:26:37,924
汉弗莱
Humphrey!

423
00:26:40,127 --> 00:26:43,164
不会吧      我有压力
No? I was under pressure!

424
00:26:45,647 --> 00:26:47,797
我们工作过度 慌慌张张
We were overworked, there was panic!

425
00:26:47,967 --> 00:26:50,242
议会就要质询了
Parliamentary questions tabled.

426
00:26:50,407 --> 00:26:52,398
显然我没受过法律训练
Obviously I'm not a trained lawyer

427
00:26:52,567 --> 00:26:57,083
不然不会派我管法务部门
or I wouldn't have been in charge of the Legal Unit!

428
00:26:58,527 --> 00:27:01,246
都30年了 人无完人啊
30 years ago! Everybody makes mistakes!

429
00:27:01,407 --> 00:27:04,319
好了 汉弗莱 我原谅你
Well, Humphrey... I forgive you.

430
00:27:08,207 --> 00:27:10,198
谢谢您 大臣
Oh, thank you, Minister.

431
00:27:10,367 --> 00:27:13,564
你怎么早不告诉我 汉弗莱?
Why didn抰 you tell me about this before?

432
00:27:13,727 --> 00:27:16,366
我们俩之间总没有秘密吧?
We have no secrets from each other, have we?

433
00:27:18,247 --> 00:27:22,206
这得由您说 大臣      不完全由我
That is for you to say, Minister. Well, not entirely.

434
00:27:22,367 --> 00:27:25,086
不过 现在要怎么办?
Anyhow, what are we gong to do?

435
00:27:25,247 --> 00:27:26,646
我会被媒体轰炸的
I'm gong to be roasted

436
00:27:26,807 --> 00:27:30,083
如果我不把所有文件给邮报
If I don't release all those papers to the Mall.

437
00:27:30,767 --> 00:27:33,679
也许我能采取些措施...
I might be able to do something about it...

438
00:27:33,847 --> 00:27:36,077
要是手头没有其他麻烦的话
If I hadn't got this other worry on my plate.

439
00:27:36,247 --> 00:27:38,238
什么其他麻烦?
What other worry

440
00:27:39,447 --> 00:27:41,278
还是被媒体轰炸
Being roasted by the press

441
00:27:41,447 --> 00:27:45,645
因为处分全国最高效的地方政府
for disciplining the most efficient council in Great Britain.

442
00:27:48,487 --> 00:27:51,206
大臣 我一直在想南德贝的事
I've been thinking about South Derbyshire.

443
00:27:53,607 --> 00:27:56,599
那敢情好      显然我们动不了法律
Oh, good. Obviously we can't change the law.

444
00:27:56,767 --> 00:27:58,678
不过也许可以宽大为怀
Perhaps we might show them leniency,

445
00:27:58,847 --> 00:28:01,042
私下跟行政长官提一句
a private word with the Chief Executive.

446
00:28:01,207 --> 00:28:04,005
给他们个机会改过
Give them a chance to mend their ways.

447
00:28:04,167 --> 00:28:06,362
这应该相当有用
That might help considerably.

448
00:28:06,527 --> 00:28:10,122
那我怎么跟邮报解释失踪的文件?
How will I explain the missing documents to the Mall?

449
00:28:10,287 --> 00:28:13,324
这个嘛 我们有种惯用手段对付...
Well, this is what we normally do in...

450
00:28:15,007 --> 00:28:16,998
这种情况
circumstances like these.

451
00:28:18,847 --> 00:28:21,441
"该档案包含全部相关文件"
"This file contains the complete set of papers,

452
00:28:21,607 --> 00:28:23,837
"除了极少数机密文件"
except for a number of secret documents,

453
00:28:24,007 --> 00:28:26,999
"少数隶属于其他未公开档案的文件"
a few others which are part of still-active files,

454
00:28:27,167 --> 00:28:31,001
"1967年洪灾中损毁的某些通信"
some correspondence lost in the floods of 1967..."

455
00:28:33,127 --> 00:28:35,516
1967年冬天很恶劣吗?
Was 1967 a particularly bad winter?

456
00:28:36,527 --> 00:28:38,040
不 那个冬天很不错
No, a marvellous winter.

457
00:28:38,207 --> 00:28:41,085
我们丢失了无数棘手的文件
We lost no end of embarrassing files.

458
00:28:42,767 --> 00:28:45,406
"运往伦敦途中遗失的某些记录"
"Records lost in the move to London,

459
00:28:45,567 --> 00:28:48,764
"战争部并入国防部期间遗失的记录"
or when the War Office joined the Ministry of Defence,

460
00:28:48,927 --> 00:28:52,522
"以及经正常程序抽出的报告 为了避免"
and the withdrawal of papers that could give grounds for an action

461
00:28:52,687 --> 00:28:54,643
"可能引起的侵害隐私"
for libel or breach of confidence

462
00:28:54,807 --> 00:28:57,685
"或冒犯友邦政府不满等情形"
or cause embarrassment to friendly governments."

463
00:28:58,727 --> 00:29:00,638
貌似很情有可原嘛
Well, that's pretty comprehensive.

464
00:29:00,807 --> 00:29:03,924
一般还能给他们剩下多少?
How many does that normally leave for them to look at?

465
00:29:04,927 --> 00:29:08,522
实际剩下了多少?
How many does it actually leave?

466
00:29:08,687 --> 00:29:11,281
大约100份? 50份?
About a hundred? Fifty?

467
00:29:12,967 --> 00:29:15,276
10份? 5份?
Ten? Five?

468
00:29:16,367 --> 00:29:18,164
4份?
Four?

469
00:29:18,327 --> 00:29:20,158
3份? 2份?
Three? Two?

470
00:29:21,607 --> 00:29:22,756
1份?
One?

471
00:29:26,207 --> 00:29:27,435
0份?
Zero?

472
00:29:28,967 --> 00:29:30,286
是 大臣
Yes, Minister.

